    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# reducer code goes into SET_OPERATION_REDUCER without function headers\n\nWhen using the `SET_OPERATION_REDUCER` MCP action, you provide only the reducer body \u2014 no function declaration, no parameter list. The framework wraps the code with the correct signature (receiving `state` and `action`).\n\n```typescript\n// \u2705 What you provide to SET_OPERATION_REDUCER\nstate.items.push({\n  id: action.input.id,\n  name: action.input.name,\n});\n\n// \u274c Don't include the function wrapper\nfunction reducer(state, action) {\n  state.items.push({ ... });\n}\n```\n\nSince [[external imports go in src reducer files not in SET_OPERATION_REDUCER]], the reducer code sent via MCP should contain no import statements either.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]\n- [[mcp workflows]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
    }
  },
